race.comment: Competitive race. BARBARIC LAD (7) broke through for a smart win at Caulfield Heath last time out, coming from well back to charge home and get up by a head. This looks another winnable race and if the tempo is on he'll be hard to hold out. SHAALUTE (3) is racing in fine form. He was beaten last time at Pakenham with 61.5kg over 1400m. Back in trip here suits better. SPARKLING (8) was fair fresh at Caulfield but should strip much fitter and finds her right race, she'll just need a good ride or for them to be coming wide in the straight which could be the case. QUISEEN (10) kicked off in a strong race first up. Up in trip suits and she's got the ability to win this from a nice draw.
